TEM, FT-IR, Zeta potential, DLS, FL, UV–vis, XRD (Fig. 2
                        ), and XPS (Fig. 3
                        ) tests were carried out to characterize the synthesized MA-CDs. As shown in Fig. 2(a), the morphological image of MA-CDs was performed by TEM. The TEM pattern presented that the prepared CDs are spherical, yet irregularly dispersed or agglomerated in some cases. It is noted that the particle size of CDs is below 10 nm, which meets the definition of CDs. Meanwhile, the lattice spacing observed through HR-TEM was about 0.21 nm, corresponding to the graphite (100) lattice plane. Furthermore, the single crystal structure of MA-CDs was confirmed by FFT diffraction images. Fig. 2(b) exhibited the specific size distribution of MA-CDs. It was interesting that the size of MA-CDs was centered around 2 nm according to the Gaussian curve of particle size distribution, which could be attributed to its corresponding fluorescence emission. Generally, it is stable with the absolute value of ζ potential at about 30 mV. From the prepared MA-CDs, the Zeta potential was around −27 mV, which was attributed to the presence of negatively charged acid and hydroxyl groups, and due to the presence of highly hydrophilic hydroxyl and carboxyl group, performed good stability in solution (Fig. 2(c)) [50].
